name: Denny Heck
tweet: On this #InternationalWomensDay we celebrate women from all walks of life.  From the lab, to the court, and especially in government, women have made strides that changed our world for the better. Today, we must continue to advocate for gender equality in all aspects of life.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Be it Further Resolved, That the Washington State Senate encourage the people of Washington State to support Ukrainian Americans and the people of Ukraine in their urgent time of need.  https://t.co/zw2Tm4Id3N

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Be it Further Resolved, That the Washington State Senate condemn the unprovoked Russian invasion of Ukraine and reiterate its support for peace, diplomacy, and an immediate end to the invasion; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Be It Further Resolved, That the Washington State Senate express its deepest sympathies for all Ukrainian Americans, especially those with loved ones in harm's way; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Now, Therefore, Be It Resolved, That the Washington State Senate recognize the democratic values shared by the people of Washington State and the people of Ukraine, and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, President Putin has denied the existence of Ukraine and apparently seeks to overthrow the democratically elected government of Ukraine and Whereas the people of Ukraine are now engaged in an armed conflict to defend their independence and democratic way of life

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, this attack on Ukraine has already killed hundreds of Ukrainian servicemembers and civilians and caused an urgent international humanitarian crisis; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, on February 24, 2022, Russian President Vladimir Putin abandoned diplomacy and international pleas for peace and launched an unprovoked military invasion of Ukraine, and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, Ukraine is the second largest country in Europe, and Whereas between 2014 and 2022, more than 14,000 Ukrainian servicemembers and civilians have been killed in armed conflict; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, Ukraine is a diverse nation, home to Ukrainians, Russians, Crimean Tatars, Jews, Poles, and many other ethnic groups; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, Ukrainian and Ukrainian Americans in Washington State have enriched our communities through their leadership and contributions in agriculture, business, academia, government, and the arts; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, Many Ukrainians immigrated to Washington State fleeing Soviet persecutions for their beliefs and for seeking personal and religious freedoms in the United States; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, Washington State is home to over 70,000 people with Ukrainian heritage and one of the largest population of Ukrainian immigrants among the 50 states; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Whereas, The people of Washington State and the people of Ukraine share a commitment to democracy. human rights, and the rule of law; and

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Today the Senate brought forward SR 8662 recognizing Ukrainian Americans and the people of Ukraine during their urgent time of need. I also met with Valeriy Goloborodko, Honorary Consul of Ukraine in Seattle, to discuss ways Washington can support the people of Ukraine.  https://t.co/yz9uhJ0zmU

name: Denny Heck
tweet: With a stellar resume, a proven record as a public defender and jurist, and an unyielding commitment to justice, Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson’s nomination to the Supreme Court is a win for all. She will be an excellent justice and I look forward to another bipartisan confirmation.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: I was privileged to lead the Senate in today's prayer. Our hearts and minds are occupied by thoughts of our brothers and sisters in Ukraine, and for those who call it home, and for all those who are suffering harm. #waleg  https://t.co/ANbfwXavGE

name: Denny Heck
tweet: The unprovoked attack by Putin against @Ukraine is a horrific display of a barbaric leader's thirst for power, and a direct challenge to the right of a sovereign nation to choose its own future. This morning I am thinking of the thousands of Washingtonians with family in Ukraine.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: This is the 80th anniversary of the signing of Executive Order 9066, which led to those forcible relocations and incarcerations. This year and every year it is important for us to pause and remember what happened to ensure it never happens again.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Today the Senate joined in virtual observance of the Day of Remembrance, an annual ceremony recognizing the incarceration of more than 120,000 persons of Japanese ancestry living on the West Coast. Thank you @senbobhasegawa for bringing forward the resolution.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: As Black History Month begins, let us recognize the Black voices, both past and present, that built our state and country into what it is today. The only way to truly honor their legacy is to continue to fight for a more just, equitable, and prosperous community for all.

name: Denny Heck

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Dr. King's profound vision of our country wasn’t met with open arms, but he and a generation of his peers persevered. We honor Dr. King's legacy by condemning racism in all its forms and advancing a more perfect union where all people experience fair treatment under our laws.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: Today the Senate formally recognized the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.  Thank you Senators Nobles for bringing forward Senate Resolution 8634 and reminding us of the courageous leadership and legacy of hope demonstrated by Dr. King throughout his life. #waleg

name: Denny Heck
tweet: People have difficulty addressing challenges in front of them when they lack access to basic necessities like a pillow, blanket, and roof. This session I'll be speaking to Senate and House committees working on housing to share the research my office has done on this issue.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: One of the most critical issues we face this #waleg session is how we address the housing shortage we have in our state. I was glad to hear @GovInslee highlight the need for developing an adequate, affordable housing supply for Washingtonians.

name: Denny Heck
tweet: The January 6th attack on the Capitol will be forever etched in our country’s memory. We watched a violent mob bend our democracy until it nearly broke, ending and shattering lives as it rampaged. It is the patriotic duty of all Americans to make sure it can never happen again.
